-- Uganda’s Former Vice President Adrisi Dies at 91: New Vision
-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 2013-07-28T14:00:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-28/uganda-s-former-vice-president-adrisi-dies-at-91-new-vision.html
General Mustafa Adrisi died today at
Mulago, the nation’s main hospital in the capital, Kampala,
where he was being treated for hypertension, diabetes and a leg
fracture, state-run New Vision says on its Twitter page.
*Adrisi served as VP from 1977-1978: Vision
*NOTE: Idi Amin, who ruled Uganda from Jan. 1971 to April 1979
died in exile in Saudi Arabia in 2003
*NOTE: Amin’s govt is accused of killing at least 300,000 people  To contact the reporter on this story:
